I wonder if this is something that I should fix, maybe by making some more significant changes to the dates. The order of events was that, after the rat magnets, Mark made a magnet for himself to test the effect, then made one for the librarian, who he'd had a crush on in high school. When that relationship didn't work out, he made one for the real estate agent (she was also a former high school crush, and he'd gotten in touch with her when he started trying to sell his parent's house), but it didn't work the same way as the others, because Mark really didn't understand how the things worked. There was some material about this that got cut, but she got really paranoid, broke into his home while he was away, and turned it on herself while she was snooping. Mark found her dead when he returned home, and, after making an initial attempt to cover it up, killed himself.





